OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNewspaper owner apologises 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffor slave trade links      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The trust which owns The Guardian has  
OL,6, apologised for its Mancunian founders' 
OL,7, links to the slave trade.              
OL,9,FThe Scott Trust said in the newspaper  
OL,10,Fmillions of pounds would be dedicated  
OL,11,Fto "descendant communities linked to   
OL,12,Fthe Guardian's 19th Century founders". 
OL,14,FResearchers had been investigating the 
OL,15,Fpaper's original Manchester financial  
OL,16,Fbackers.                               
OL,18,FThey found partnerships within the     
OL,19,Ftextile industry linked to cotton      
OL,20,Fproduced by enslaved people.           
